1
00:00:01,720 --> 00:00:04,000
(THUNDER CRASHING)

2
00:00:04,160 --> 00:00:06,680
DARLA: First there were the Daleks.

3
00:00:07,600 --> 00:00:10,360
And then there was a man
who fought them.

4
00:00:12,920 --> 00:00:14,600
And then, in time,

5
00:00:15,200 --> 00:00:16,560
he died.

6
00:00:17,320 --> 00:00:21,600
There are a few, of course,
who believe this man somehow survived

7
00:00:21,680 --> 00:00:24,480
and that one day he will return.

8
00:00:25,440 --> 00:00:30,920
For both our sakes, dearest Hannah,
we must hope these stories are true.

9
00:00:38,320 --> 00:00:41,840
I got your message.
Not many people can do that,

10
00:00:43,320 --> 00:00:44,720
send me messages.

11
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:46,680
I have a daughter,

12
00:00:47,520 --> 00:00:48,720
Hannah.

13
00:00:49,080 --> 00:00:51,200
She's in a Dalek prison camp.

14
00:00:51,680 --> 00:00:53,440
They say you can help.

15
00:00:53,520 --> 00:00:56,600
Do they? I wish they'd stop.

16
00:00:58,280 --> 00:01:00,000
Hell of a choice of meeting place.

17
00:01:00,080 --> 00:01:01,920
They said I'd have to intrigue you.

18
00:01:03,080 --> 00:01:07,040
DOCTOR: Skaro.
The original planet of the Daleks.

19
00:01:07,720 --> 00:01:09,080
Look at the state of it.

20
00:01:11,360 --> 00:01:13,520
-Who told you about me?
-Does it matter?

21
00:01:13,600 --> 00:01:17,040
Maybe not.
But you're very well-informed.

22
00:01:26,920 --> 00:01:30,680
If Hannah's in a Dalek prison camp,
tell me, why aren't you?

23
00:01:31,560 --> 00:01:35,000
-I escaped.
-(LAUGHING) No!

24
00:01:36,160 --> 00:01:38,440
Nobody escapes the Dalek camps.

25
00:01:39,360 --> 00:01:40,560
You're very cold.

26
00:01:43,400 --> 00:01:44,840
What's wrong?

27
00:01:45,200 --> 00:01:47,200
-It's a trap.
-What is?

28
00:01:47,800 --> 00:01:50,720
-You are. And you don't even know it.
-(NECK CRACKING)

29
00:01:57,880 --> 00:01:59,000
(SCREAMING)

30
00:02:02,680 --> 00:02:05,000
DALEX: The Doctor is acquired!

31
00:02:05,760 --> 00:02:08,280
(POP MUSIC PLAYING, CAMERA CLICKING)

32
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:19,840
I'll just be a minute.

33
00:02:22,080 --> 00:02:25,640
-Um, your husband is here.
-Hmm. I don't have a husband.

34
00:02:26,400 --> 00:02:28,960
Oh, well, apparently you still do.

35
00:02:29,880 --> 00:02:31,080
(SIGHS)

36
00:02:32,040 --> 00:02:33,200
(EXHALES)

37
00:02:33,280 --> 00:02:34,640
You have to sign these.

38
00:02:36,880 --> 00:02:38,200
And then we're not married?

39
00:02:38,280 --> 00:02:40,000
Just like magic.

40
00:02:41,560 --> 00:02:43,800
-Can't chat, working.
-Really?

41
00:02:44,640 --> 00:02:47,440
I thought you were just
pouting at a camera.

42
00:02:48,600 --> 00:02:49,720
Rory...

43
00:02:49,960 --> 00:02:51,720
(LIGHT BULB BUZZING)

44
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:53,560
Sorry, love. Was I interrupting?

45
00:02:53,880 --> 00:02:54,960
No.

46
00:02:55,240 --> 00:02:57,600
Gosh, look at you. You've gone so pale.

47
00:02:57,680 --> 00:02:59,480
Come on. Take a seat.

48
00:02:59,920 --> 00:03:01,440
We'll soon sort that out.

49
00:03:02,720 --> 00:03:04,000
(BUZZING)

50
00:03:05,200 --> 00:03:06,880
(NECK CRACKING)

51
00:03:14,560 --> 00:03:17,080
Amelia Pond is acquired!

52
00:03:22,400 --> 00:03:23,600
Cheers.

53
00:03:29,720 --> 00:03:31,040
(NECK CRACKING)

54
00:03:34,920 --> 00:03:37,480
Rory Williams is acquired!

55
00:03:43,640 --> 00:03:44,840
(GASPS)

56
00:03:46,560 --> 00:03:48,000
Where are we?

57
00:03:57,920 --> 00:04:00,160
So how much trouble are we in?

58
00:04:00,480 --> 00:04:02,320
(DOOR WHIRRING)

59
00:04:04,560 --> 00:04:06,640
DOCTOR: How much trouble, Mr Pond?

60
00:04:10,040 --> 00:04:11,160
Out of 107

61
00:04:15,600 --> 00:04:16,640
11.

62
00:04:17,200 --> 00:04:18,640
(HATCH WHIRRING)

63
00:04:35,680 --> 00:04:37,040
(METALLIC CLANG)

64
00:04:48,880 --> 00:04:51,320
Where are we? Spaceship, right?

65
00:04:51,640 --> 00:04:53,560
Not just any spaceship.

66
00:04:56,840 --> 00:04:58,320
The Parliament of the Daleks.

67
00:04:59,440 --> 00:05:00,720
Be brave.

68
00:05:01,080 --> 00:05:02,320
What do we do?

69
00:05:02,400 --> 00:05:04,600
Make them remember you.

70
00:05:07,360 --> 00:05:09,120
Well, come on, then.

71
00:05:10,800 --> 00:05:11,960
You've got me.

72
00:05:12,880 --> 00:05:14,600
What are you waiting for?

73
00:05:14,680 --> 00:05:18,680
At long last, it's Christmas!

74
00:05:19,960 --> 00:05:21,360
Here I am!

75
00:05:26,880 --> 00:05:28,640
Save us.

76
00:05:33,520 --> 00:05:36,360
You will save us.

77
00:05:37,600 --> 00:05:38,720
I'll what?

78
00:05:38,800 --> 00:05:42,000
You will save the Daleks.

79
00:05:42,320 --> 00:05:45,920
-Save the Daleks!
-Save the Daleks!

80
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:47,800
ALL: Save the Daleks!/

81
00:05:48,280 --> 00:05:51,720
Save the Daleks! Save the Daleks!

82
00:05:52,040 --> 00:05:55,000
Save the Daleks! Save the Daleks!

83
00:05:55,080 --> 00:05:56,280
Well...

84
00:05:56,360 --> 00:05:57,600
(CHANTING CONTINUES)

85
00:05:57,680 --> 00:05:59,080
This is new.

86
00:05:59,200 --> 00:06:01,000
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

87
00:06:35,200 --> 00:06:37,280
(CARMEN SUITE NO. 2 PLAYING)

88
00:06:37,360 --> 00:06:39,720
OSWIN: Day 3635.

89
00:06:39,800 --> 00:06:42,120
-(HUMMING)
-The terror continues.

90
00:06:45,840 --> 00:06:47,000
Also, made another souffle.

91
00:06:47,080 --> 00:06:48,480
(BELL DINGS)

92
00:06:51,240 --> 00:06:52,640
Very nearly.

93
00:06:59,200 --> 00:07:00,720
Check defences.

94
00:07:02,120 --> 00:07:05,840
They came again last night.
Still always at night.

95
00:07:07,240 --> 00:07:09,160
Maybe they're vampires.

96
00:07:11,480 --> 00:07:14,160
(GASPS) Oh! And it's my mum's birthday.

97
00:07:15,760 --> 00:07:16,840
Happy birthday, Mum.

98
00:07:19,200 --> 00:07:21,560
I did make you a souffle
but it was too beautiful to live.

99
00:07:21,640 --> 00:07:25,800
DALEK: (BANGING) You will let us enter!

100
00:07:25,880 --> 00:07:30,040
DALEKS: We will enter! We will enter!

101
00:07:30,120 --> 00:07:32,080
(PLAYING CARMEN SUITE NO. 7 LOUDLY)

102
00:07:33,320 --> 00:07:35,880
(DALEKS SHOUTING, INDISTINCT)

103
00:07:36,160 --> 00:07:38,240
(BANGING CONTINUES)

104
00:07:42,480 --> 00:07:44,040
RORY: What's he doing?

105
00:07:44,120 --> 00:07:46,280
AMY: He's chosen the most
defendable area in the room,

106
00:07:46,360 --> 00:07:47,880
counted all the Daleks,
counted all the exits

107
00:07:47,960 --> 00:07:50,480
and now he's calculating
the exact distance we're standing apart

108
00:07:50,560 --> 00:07:52,400
and he's starting to worry.

109
00:07:52,480 --> 00:07:54,800
Oh! And look at him frowning now.

110
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:58,080
"Something's wrong with Amy and Rory
and who's going to fix it?"

111
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:02,000
And he straightens his bow tie.

112
00:08:02,320 --> 00:08:04,520
DALEK: We have arrived.

113
00:08:08,520 --> 00:08:09,640
Arrived where?

114
00:08:10,080 --> 00:08:11,280
Doctor.

115
00:08:12,240 --> 00:08:15,080
The Prime Minister
will speak with you now.

116
00:08:18,440 --> 00:08:19,680
Do you remember who you were

117
00:08:19,760 --> 00:08:23,360
before they emptied you out
and turned you into their puppet?

118
00:08:23,440 --> 00:08:25,120
My memories are only reactivated

119
00:08:25,200 --> 00:08:28,080
if they are required to facilitate
deep cover or disguise.

120
00:08:29,320 --> 00:08:31,240
-You had a daughter.
-I know.

121
00:08:32,120 --> 00:08:33,160
I've read my file.

122
00:08:49,320 --> 00:08:50,400
Well?

123
00:08:51,120 --> 00:08:55,800
What do you know of the Dalek asylum?

124
00:08:56,040 --> 00:08:59,080
According to legend,
you have a dumping ground.

125
00:08:59,800 --> 00:09:02,360
A planet where you lock up
all the Daleks that go wrong.

126
00:09:03,440 --> 00:09:05,720
The battle-scarred, the insane,

127
00:09:06,600 --> 00:09:08,920
the ones even you can't control.

128
00:09:10,400 --> 00:09:12,000
Which never made any sense to me.

129
00:09:12,080 --> 00:09:14,040
-Why not?
-Because you'd just kill them.

130
00:09:14,320 --> 00:09:19,920
It is offensive to us
to extinguish such divine hatred.

131
00:09:20,720 --> 00:09:22,040
Offensive?

132
00:09:22,440 --> 00:09:28,440
Does it surprise you to know
that Daleks have a concept of beauty?

133
00:09:29,080 --> 00:09:33,080
I thought you'd run out of ways
to make me sick.

134
00:09:33,400 --> 00:09:35,000
But hello again.

135
00:09:37,080 --> 00:09:40,680
You think hatred is beautiful?

136
00:09:42,480 --> 00:09:47,520
Perhaps that is why
we have never been able to kill you.

137
00:09:49,840 --> 00:09:51,280
(METALLIC CLANGING)

138
00:09:59,040 --> 00:10:02,040
DARLA: The asylum.
It occupies the entire planet,

139
00:10:03,040 --> 00:10:04,720
right to the core.

140
00:10:05,880 --> 00:10:07,480
DOCTOR: How many Daleks are in there?

141
00:10:07,560 --> 00:10:10,520
DARLA: A count has not been made.
Millions, certainly.

142
00:10:10,600 --> 00:10:13,760
DOCTOR: All still alive?
DARLA: It has to be assumed.

143
00:10:13,840 --> 00:10:15,680
The asylum is fully automated.

144
00:10:15,760 --> 00:10:18,280
-Supervision is not required.
-Armed?

145
00:10:18,600 --> 00:10:19,760
The Daleks are always armed.

146
00:10:19,840 --> 00:10:21,240
What colour?

147
00:10:24,520 --> 00:10:25,760
Sorry, there weren't
any good questions left.

148
00:10:25,840 --> 00:10:26,880
(SIGNAL BLEEPING)

149
00:10:26,960 --> 00:10:29,560
DARLA: This signal is being received
from the very heart of the asylum.

150
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:33,000
(BIZET'S CARMEN PLAYING)

151
00:10:37,920 --> 00:10:42,720
What is the noise? Explain! Explain!

152
00:10:42,800 --> 00:10:45,600
-It's me.
-Sorry, what?

153
00:10:46,200 --> 00:10:48,760
It's me playing the triangle. (LAUGHS)

154
00:10:48,840 --> 00:10:50,320
Okay, I got buried in the mix.

155
00:10:50,880 --> 00:10:53,520
Carmen, lovely show.

156
00:10:54,840 --> 00:10:56,360
Someone's transmitting this.

157
00:10:56,440 --> 00:11:01,040
Have you considered tracking
back the signal and talking to them?

158
00:11:01,560 --> 00:11:03,680
(OPERA CONTINUES PLAYING)

159
00:11:04,240 --> 00:11:06,000
He asked the Daleks.

160
00:11:06,520 --> 00:11:08,280
Hello? Hello, Carmen!

161
00:11:08,680 --> 00:11:09,800
Hello!

162
00:11:10,160 --> 00:11:12,560
-Hello?
-Come in, come in. Come in, Carmen.

163
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:16,480
Hello! Yes, yes! Sorry. Do you read me?

164
00:11:16,840 --> 00:11:18,080
Yes! Reading you loud and clear.

165
00:11:18,160 --> 00:11:20,920
Identify yourself
and report your status.

166
00:11:21,400 --> 00:11:22,560
Hello.

167
00:11:23,280 --> 00:11:24,680
Are you real?

168
00:11:24,760 --> 00:11:26,680
Are you actually, properly real?

169
00:11:26,960 --> 00:11:29,560
Yeah, confirmed.
Actually, properly real.

170
00:11:29,640 --> 00:11:32,320
Oswin Oswald.
Junior Entertainment Manager,

171
00:11:32,400 --> 00:11:36,120
Starship Alaska. Current status,
crashed and shipwrecked somewhere...

172
00:11:37,320 --> 00:11:38,440
not nice.

173
00:11:38,520 --> 00:11:39,880
Been here a year,
rest of the crew missing,

174
00:11:39,960 --> 00:11:41,480
provision's good but keen to move on.

175
00:11:41,840 --> 00:11:43,040
A year?

176
00:11:43,720 --> 00:11:46,200
Are you okay? Are you under attack?

177
00:11:46,400 --> 00:11:47,720
Some local life forms.

178
00:11:49,160 --> 00:11:50,320
Been keeping them out.

179
00:11:50,400 --> 00:11:51,960
Do you know what those life forms are?

180
00:11:52,040 --> 00:11:54,080
I know a Dalek when I hear one, yeah.

181
00:11:54,160 --> 00:11:58,640
What have you been doing
on your own against the Daleks

182
00:11:58,720 --> 00:12:00,000
for a year?

183
00:12:00,760 --> 00:12:01,800
Making souffles.

184
00:12:02,520 --> 00:12:05,120
Souffles. Against the Daleks. (CHUCKLES)

185
00:12:07,160 --> 00:12:08,240
Where do you get the milk?

186
00:12:08,320 --> 00:12:11,080
This conversation is irrelevant.

187
00:12:11,160 --> 00:12:12,560
No, it isn't!

188
00:12:12,840 --> 00:12:15,040
-(SIGNAL WARBLING)
-Hello! Hello! Hello!

189
00:12:15,760 --> 00:12:19,240
Because a star line has crashed
into your asylum and someone's got in.

190
00:12:19,320 --> 00:12:22,200
And if someone can get in,
then everything can get out.

191
00:12:22,280 --> 00:12:24,800
A tsunami of insane Daleks.

192
00:12:24,960 --> 00:12:26,040
Even you don't want that.

193
00:12:26,120 --> 00:12:29,920
-The asylum must be cleansed.
-Then why is it still here?

194
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:33,240
You've enough firepower on this ship
to blast it out of the sky.

195
00:12:33,320 --> 00:12:35,240
The asylum force field is impenetrable.

196
00:12:35,320 --> 00:12:36,440
Turn it off.

197
00:12:36,520 --> 00:12:38,520
It can only be turned off
from within the asylum.

198
00:12:39,320 --> 00:12:42,600
A small task force
could sneak through a force field.

199
00:12:42,680 --> 00:12:44,760
Send in a couple of Daleks.

200
00:12:48,200 --> 00:12:49,240
Oh!

201
00:12:52,560 --> 00:12:55,200
Oh! Ah, that's good, that's brilliant.

202
00:12:55,480 --> 00:12:57,680
You're all too scared to go down there.

203
00:12:58,360 --> 00:13:01,040
Not one of you will go, so tell me.

204
00:13:02,960 --> 00:13:05,640
What do the Daleks do
when they're too scared?

205
00:13:06,040 --> 00:13:10,120
The Predator of the Daleks
will be deployed.

206
00:13:10,200 --> 00:13:11,280
You don't have a predator.

207
00:13:11,360 --> 00:13:13,760
And even if you did, why would
they turn off a force field for you?

208
00:13:14,080 --> 00:13:18,400
Because you will have
no other means of escape.

209
00:13:18,920 --> 00:13:20,400
May I clarify?

210
00:13:20,560 --> 00:13:22,560
The Predator is a Dalek's word for you.

211
00:13:22,920 --> 00:13:25,320
Me? Me?

212
00:13:26,600 --> 00:13:29,600
You will need this.
It will protect you from the nanocloud.

213
00:13:29,680 --> 00:13:31,400
The what? The nano what?

214
00:13:31,480 --> 00:13:35,240
The gravity beam will convey you
close to the source of the transmission.

215
00:13:35,320 --> 00:13:37,600
You must find a way to deactivate
the force field from there.

216
00:13:37,680 --> 00:13:41,160
You're going to fire me at a planet?
That's your plan?

217
00:13:41,280 --> 00:13:44,240
I get fired at a planet
and expected to fix it?

218
00:13:44,440 --> 00:13:46,280
In fairness, that is slightly your MO.

219
00:13:46,360 --> 00:13:49,160
Don't be fair to the Daleks
when they're firing me at a planet.

220
00:13:49,960 --> 00:13:51,680
What do you want with them?

221
00:13:51,760 --> 00:13:55,960
It is known
that the Doctor requires companions.

222
00:13:56,040 --> 00:13:58,120
Oh, brilliant! Good-o!

223
00:13:58,200 --> 00:13:59,560
DOCTOR: Don't worry.

224
00:13:59,640 --> 00:14:02,040
We'll get through this, I promise.
Don't be scared.

225
00:14:02,120 --> 00:14:04,440
Scared? Who's scared?

226
00:14:05,800 --> 00:14:07,520
Geronimo.

227
00:14:07,800 --> 00:14:09,600
-DOCTOR: Oi!
-(AMY AND RORY SCREAMING)

228
00:14:10,440 --> 00:14:11,960
(ALL SCREAMING)

229
00:14:14,800 --> 00:14:16,360
Wrong way up! Wrong way up!

230
00:14:17,000 --> 00:14:18,560
Oh, God!

231
00:14:20,240 --> 00:14:21,600
Rory!

232
00:14:31,000 --> 00:14:32,760
(ALL SCREAMING)

233
00:14:37,080 --> 00:14:38,440
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

234
00:14:42,760 --> 00:14:44,240
(PANTING)

235
00:14:46,520 --> 00:14:48,000
(AMY MUMBLING)

236
00:14:52,360 --> 00:14:53,520
Hello.

237
00:14:54,080 --> 00:14:56,400
-Hello. Who are you?
-(AMY GASPS)

238
00:14:57,160 --> 00:14:58,920
-You okay?
-(GASPING)

239
00:15:05,440 --> 00:15:07,080
Rory? (PANTING)

240
00:15:07,480 --> 00:15:09,160
Doctor? (PANTING)

241
00:15:09,440 --> 00:15:11,240
I'm Harvey. I'm Harv...

242
00:15:12,120 --> 00:15:13,480
Who's Rory?

243
00:15:14,600 --> 00:15:16,320
Where are you going?

244
00:15:19,680 --> 00:15:21,000
(WHIRRING)

245
00:15:34,840 --> 00:15:35,920
(GRUNTING)

246
00:15:39,000 --> 00:15:40,240
(LAUGHS)

247
00:15:44,560 --> 00:15:46,040
Hey! Huh?

248
00:15:49,720 --> 00:15:51,720
(CARMEN PLAYING)

249
00:15:56,440 --> 00:15:59,200
OSWIN: Sorry.
Sorry, pressed the wrong switch.

250
00:15:59,280 --> 00:16:00,520
Souffle Girl?

251
00:16:01,080 --> 00:16:03,480
You could always call me Oswin,
seeing as that's my name.

252
00:16:04,000 --> 00:16:05,480
AR/
-You okay?

253
00:16:07,560 --> 00:16:09,640
How are you doing that, eh?

254
00:16:09,760 --> 00:16:11,120
This is Dalek technology.

255
00:16:12,400 --> 00:16:15,200
-Well, it's very easy to hack.
-No, it isn't.

256
00:16:15,840 --> 00:16:16,920
Where are you?

257
00:16:17,000 --> 00:16:20,400
Ship broke up when it hit.
Somewhere underground, I think.

258
00:16:20,480 --> 00:16:21,560
You coming to get me?

259
00:16:21,640 --> 00:16:23,040
AMY: Doctor?

260
00:16:23,600 --> 00:16:26,120
Hey! Oi, Souffle Girl!

261
00:16:26,480 --> 00:16:28,120
-Come back.
-Damn!

262
00:16:28,760 --> 00:16:30,520
Doctor!

263
00:16:30,600 --> 00:16:31,680
Amy.

264
00:16:33,040 --> 00:16:34,080
-Hey.
-(PANTING)

265
00:16:35,920 --> 00:16:38,880
-Where's Rory?
-HARVEY: There was another beam.

266
00:16:39,920 --> 00:16:41,600
There. Over there.

267
00:16:43,680 --> 00:16:45,720
Are you the rescue team?

268
00:16:46,880 --> 00:16:48,520
(TOGGLING SWITCHES, SIGNAL WARBLING)

269
00:16:48,600 --> 00:16:49,760
Hello!

270
00:16:56,520 --> 00:16:58,240
AMY: Rory?

271
00:17:01,520 --> 00:17:02,640
Rory!

272
00:17:05,640 --> 00:17:08,120
Rory!

273
00:17:10,440 --> 00:17:13,000
(WATER TRICKLING, RORY MOANING)

274
00:17:18,520 --> 00:17:19,720
(GASPS)

275
00:17:25,320 --> 00:17:26,320
(EXHALES)

276
00:17:51,920 --> 00:17:53,120
(GASPS)

277
00:18:03,440 --> 00:18:04,520
Hmm.

278
00:18:15,600 --> 00:18:19,360
We came down two days ago.
There's 12 other escape pods.

279
00:18:20,600 --> 00:18:22,200
(LOCKS CLICKING)

280
00:18:22,400 --> 00:18:23,720
(WHIRRING)

281
00:18:23,800 --> 00:18:26,080
HARVEY: I don't know
what happened to them.

282
00:18:26,160 --> 00:18:29,000
AMY: Alaska?
That's the same ship as Souffle Girl.

283
00:18:29,080 --> 00:18:30,520
DOCTOR: Yeah.

284
00:18:31,160 --> 00:18:33,160
Except she's been here a year.

285
00:18:37,520 --> 00:18:42,440
Here, we should have some climbing rope
long enough for that hole.

286
00:18:47,440 --> 00:18:49,960
Won't you introduce us to your crew?

287
00:18:50,240 --> 00:18:53,040
Ah, yeah, sorry.
Guys, this is the Doctor and Amy.

288
00:18:57,160 --> 00:18:58,280
Guys?

289
00:19:05,720 --> 00:19:07,280
HARVEY: Oh, my God!

290
00:19:16,040 --> 00:19:17,480
They're dead.

291
00:19:17,680 --> 00:19:19,760
-All of them.
-That's not possible.

292
00:19:19,840 --> 00:19:21,560
I just spoke to them.

293
00:19:22,160 --> 00:19:23,880
Two hours ago,
we were doing engine repairs.

294
00:19:27,200 --> 00:19:29,200
You're sure about that, are you?

295
00:19:30,200 --> 00:19:33,840
'Cause I'd say they've all been dead
for a very long time.

296
00:19:34,120 --> 00:19:35,360
Well, they can't be.

297
00:19:35,600 --> 00:19:38,200
Well, they didn't get in this state
in two hours.

298
00:19:38,280 --> 00:19:40,680
Oh, of course. Stupid me.

299
00:19:41,400 --> 00:19:42,560
Of course what?

300
00:19:43,160 --> 00:19:44,400
I died outside.

301
00:19:46,040 --> 00:19:47,760
And the cold preserved my body.

302
00:19:49,920 --> 00:19:51,960
I forgot about dying.

303
00:19:56,120 --> 00:19:57,480
(SCREAMING)

304
00:19:58,600 --> 00:20:00,200
-Amy, the door!
-Come on, come on!

305
00:20:07,000 --> 00:20:10,160
Explain, that's what you're good at,
how did he get all Daleked?

306
00:20:10,240 --> 00:20:12,320
Because he wasn't wearing one of these.

307
00:20:12,400 --> 00:20:14,040
Oh, ho, ho!

308
00:20:14,120 --> 00:20:17,360
That's clever! The nanocloud.

309
00:20:17,560 --> 00:20:20,760
Microorganisms that automatically
process any organic matter,

310
00:20:20,840 --> 00:20:23,560
living or dead, into a Dalek puppet.

311
00:20:24,160 --> 00:20:26,240
(CHUCKLES) Anything attacks this place

312
00:20:26,320 --> 00:20:28,920
it automatically becomes part
of the on-site security.

313
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:31,600
-Living or dead?
-These wristbands protect us.

314
00:20:31,680 --> 00:20:33,240
The only thing stopping us
going exactly the way he did...

315
00:20:33,320 --> 00:20:34,840
Doctor, shut up.

316
00:20:34,920 --> 00:20:36,760
-Living or dead?
-Yes, exactly, living or-or-or...

317
00:20:36,840 --> 00:20:37,880
(BONES CRACKING)

318
00:20:39,080 --> 00:20:40,880
(CRACKING)

319
00:20:42,960 --> 00:20:44,080
...dead.

320
00:20:45,480 --> 00:20:46,520
Oh, dear.

321
00:20:48,560 --> 00:20:51,440
(BANGING ON DOOR)

322
00:20:51,520 --> 00:20:52,680
Yeah.

323
00:20:52,880 --> 00:20:54,200
(GRUNTING)

324
00:20:54,800 --> 00:20:56,320
(AMY EXCLAIMING)

325
00:20:59,920 --> 00:21:01,680
(SCREAMS) Doctor!

326
00:21:02,360 --> 00:21:03,680
(GRUNTING)

327
00:21:04,960 --> 00:21:06,160
(PANTING)

328
00:21:10,560 --> 00:21:13,320
-Is it bad that I've really missed this?
-Yes.

329
00:21:13,400 --> 00:21:14,800
-It's good.
-I know.

330
00:21:15,760 --> 00:21:18,560
(OVER PA) Unauthorised personnel
may not enter the cockpit.

331
00:21:18,640 --> 00:21:21,040
-Shut up.
-What? Mr Grumpy.

332
00:21:21,680 --> 00:21:24,080
Bad combo.
No sense of humour and that chin.

333
00:21:24,360 --> 00:21:25,680
Is that her again, Souffleey Girl?

334
00:21:26,040 --> 00:21:28,480
Yeah, she...
Oi, what is wrong with my chin?

335
00:21:28,720 --> 00:21:30,400
Careful, dear.
You'll put someone's eye out.

336
00:21:31,000 --> 00:21:32,120
I'm scanning you.

337
00:21:32,200 --> 00:21:33,520
You're in another of the escape pods
from the Alaska,

338
00:21:33,600 --> 00:21:34,640
it seems your power's on.

339
00:21:34,720 --> 00:21:37,160
How can you hack into everything?
It should be impossible.

340
00:21:37,240 --> 00:21:39,520
-You're in a crashed ship!
-Long story.

341
00:21:40,440 --> 00:21:42,000
Is there a word for
"total screaming genius”

342
00:21:42,080 --> 00:21:44,240
that sounds modest and a tiny bit sexy?

343
00:21:44,320 --> 00:21:47,800
Doctor. You call me the Doctor.

344
00:21:47,880 --> 00:21:49,120
-See what you did there.
-(BEEPING)

345
00:21:49,200 --> 00:21:50,880
Check the floor.
I'm picking up a breach at floor level.

346
00:21:50,960 --> 00:21:53,080
There could be a way out.
See you later.

347
00:21:54,040 --> 00:21:56,600
A-ha! Hatch.
It looks like it's been used already

348
00:21:56,680 --> 00:21:58,360
and they tried to block it off
behind them.

349
00:21:58,440 --> 00:22:00,440
-(BANGING ON DOOR)
-Can't imagine why.

350
00:22:00,520 --> 00:22:01,840
The lower part of the pod is buried,

351
00:22:01,920 --> 00:22:04,800
so this must go
straight down to the asylum.

352
00:22:05,080 --> 00:22:06,560
Where Rory is.

353
00:22:06,880 --> 00:22:10,200
Yeah. Speaking of Rory... (GRUNTS)
Is there anything you want to tell me?

354
00:22:10,280 --> 00:22:12,600
-Are we going to do this now?
-Well, what happened?

355
00:22:12,680 --> 00:22:15,840
Oh, stuff, you know.
We split up. What can you do?

356
00:22:16,760 --> 00:22:18,240
What can I do?

357
00:22:19,360 --> 00:22:20,600
Nothing.

358
00:22:21,720 --> 00:22:25,080
It's not one of those things you can fix
like you fix your bow tie.

359
00:22:25,760 --> 00:22:29,200
And don't give me those big, wet eyes,
raggedy man. It's life.

360
00:22:29,560 --> 00:22:32,200
Just life. That thing that goes on
when you're not there.

361
00:22:32,520 --> 00:22:34,840
-(METAL CLANKS)
-Right...

362
00:22:36,080 --> 00:22:37,400
(GRUNTING)

363
00:22:39,440 --> 00:22:41,360
Okay, so someone else
got out this way, then.

364
00:22:41,440 --> 00:22:43,040
-Yeah, let's go and find them.
-(POUNDING ON DOOR CONTINUES)

365
00:22:43,120 --> 00:22:46,600
Whoa! Hello, hello, hello.
What are they up to?

366
00:22:47,200 --> 00:22:48,320
What's that?

367
00:22:48,920 --> 00:22:51,440
One of these. But where did they get it?

368
00:22:54,520 --> 00:22:55,880
Oh, Doctor.

369
00:22:57,440 --> 00:23:00,080
-They got it from me.
-Oh, Amy.

370
00:23:00,880 --> 00:23:04,640
Doctor, what's going to happen to me,
seriously? Tell me. What?

371
00:23:07,320 --> 00:23:08,640
(BANGING ON DOOR)

372
00:23:51,720 --> 00:23:52,840
Ah.

373
00:23:55,760 --> 00:23:56,960
(METAL CLANKS)

374
00:23:59,240 --> 00:24:00,320
Shh.

375
00:24:02,280 --> 00:24:03,960
(METAL SCREECHING)

376
00:24:05,520 --> 00:24:06,600
Shh.

377
00:24:08,440 --> 00:24:10,920
"Egg-egg-egg-egg-egg-egg-eggs...”

378
00:24:12,800 --> 00:24:13,920
What?

379
00:24:15,280 --> 00:24:16,440
Sorry, what?

380
00:24:16,800 --> 00:24:19,040
"Egg-egg-egg-egg-egg-eggs...”

381
00:24:19,320 --> 00:24:20,360
Eggs?

382
00:24:21,840 --> 00:24:24,880
-You mean those things?
_IIEggs.-- FF

383
00:24:25,600 --> 00:24:28,680
I don't... I don't know what you want.

384
00:24:28,760 --> 00:24:32,640
Uh, those things...
Are those things eggs?

385
00:24:33,880 --> 00:24:35,000
This?

386
00:24:35,600 --> 00:24:37,080
You want this?

387
00:24:37,520 --> 00:24:39,440
IIEggs.-- Fr

388
00:24:40,960 --> 00:24:44,720
(SLOWLY) ...term...i...

389
00:24:45,880 --> 00:24:48,120
...Nate.

390
00:24:49,880 --> 00:24:54,480
-Exterminate!
-Exterminate!

391
00:24:55,600 --> 00:24:56,760
(EXCLAIMS)

392
00:24:56,920 --> 00:24:59,880
Exterminate!

393
00:25:00,360 --> 00:25:02,560
(DALEKS CONTINUE SHOUTING)

394
00:25:02,760 --> 00:25:04,080
(GRUNTING)

395
00:25:04,320 --> 00:25:06,400
ALL: Exterminate! Exterminate!

396
00:25:06,880 --> 00:25:09,200
OSWIN: (OVER PA)
Run! The door at the end. Run for it/

397
00:25:09,360 --> 00:25:12,040
They're waking up but they're slow.
The door at the end. Just run.

398
00:25:12,480 --> 00:25:13,880
Now, now, now!

399
00:25:14,080 --> 00:25:17,280
DALEK: Exterminate! Exterminate!

400
00:25:19,000 --> 00:25:20,680
Exterminate!

401
00:25:20,760 --> 00:25:22,600
(SCREAMING)

402
00:25:23,680 --> 00:25:26,640
Exterminate! Extermin...

403
00:25:27,640 --> 00:25:28,960
(EXHALING)

404
00:25:30,040 --> 00:25:31,320
(SIGHING)

405
00:25:32,640 --> 00:25:33,880
-So. Anyway.
-(GASPS)

406
00:25:34,200 --> 00:25:36,440
-I'm Oswin. What do I call you?
-Uh...

407
00:25:36,720 --> 00:25:39,040
I can't remember. Uh...

408
00:25:39,240 --> 00:25:40,280
Rory.

409
00:25:40,480 --> 00:25:41,920
Lovely name, Rory.

410
00:25:42,720 --> 00:25:44,880
First boy I ever fancied
was called Rory.

411
00:25:44,960 --> 00:25:47,120
-Okay.
-Actually, she was called Nina.

412
00:25:47,680 --> 00:25:49,800
I was going through a phase.

413
00:25:49,960 --> 00:25:52,440
Just flirting to keep you cheerful.

414
00:25:52,520 --> 00:25:54,000
(LOUD BANGING)

415
00:25:54,880 --> 00:25:56,840
DALEKS: (MUFFLED) Exterminate!

416
00:25:57,000 --> 00:26:02,160
DALEKS: Exterminate!
Exterminate! Exterminate!

417
00:26:05,400 --> 00:26:06,920
Ah, okay.

418
00:26:08,520 --> 00:26:11,200
(WHISPERING) Anytime you want to start
flirting again is fine by me.

419
00:26:12,600 --> 00:26:16,280
So tell me. What's going to happen
to me? And don't lie.

420
00:26:16,360 --> 00:26:18,920
'Cause I know when you're lying to me
and I will definitely fall on you.

421
00:26:19,000 --> 00:26:21,640
The air all around
is full of micro-machines,

422
00:26:21,880 --> 00:26:23,680
robots the size of molecules.

423
00:26:24,240 --> 00:26:25,560
Nanogenes.

424
00:26:25,880 --> 00:26:27,360
Now that you're unprotected,

425
00:26:27,960 --> 00:26:30,160
you're being...rewritten.

426
00:26:31,120 --> 00:26:33,760
So what happens? I get one of those
things sticking out of my head?

427
00:26:33,840 --> 00:26:37,040
-Physical changes come later.
-What comes first? How does it start?

428
00:26:37,120 --> 00:26:39,480
With your mind.
Your feelings, your memories.

429
00:26:39,560 --> 00:26:43,160
-And I'm sorry but it's started already.
-How do you know?

430
00:26:43,240 --> 00:26:45,640
Because we've had this conversation
four times.

431
00:26:45,720 --> 00:26:47,680
Okay, I'm scared now.

432
00:26:48,240 --> 00:26:50,880
Hang on to scared. Scared isn't Dalek.

433
00:27:01,400 --> 00:27:02,720
(WHIRRING)

434
00:27:03,560 --> 00:27:05,720
OSWIN: Hey there, Binky boy.

435
00:27:06,360 --> 00:27:08,280
If it's a straight choice,
I prefer Nina.

436
00:27:08,560 --> 00:27:10,960
Loving this! The nose and the chin.

437
00:27:11,480 --> 00:27:13,480
You two could fence.

438
00:27:13,680 --> 00:27:15,480
There's a door behind you.

439
00:27:18,680 --> 00:27:20,320
In there, quickly.

440
00:27:22,600 --> 00:27:24,200
Okay. You're safe for now.

441
00:27:24,720 --> 00:27:25,920
Pop your shirt off, quick as you like.

442
00:27:26,600 --> 00:27:28,720
-Why?
-Does there have to be a reason?

443
00:27:30,280 --> 00:27:32,240
(METAL CLANKING)

444
00:27:34,000 --> 00:27:35,320
(SNIFFING)

445
00:27:35,880 --> 00:27:37,880
(DALEKS SHOUTING IN DISTANCE)

446
00:27:38,000 --> 00:27:39,200
AMY: What's that?

447
00:27:39,360 --> 00:27:41,600
(DALEKS SHOUTING, INDISTINCT)

448
00:27:43,920 --> 00:27:46,960
Keep a look out, don't open this door.
Oswin!

449
00:27:48,560 --> 00:27:50,280
Oswin, can you hear me?

450
00:27:50,360 --> 00:27:53,000
Hello, The Chin, I have visual on you.

451
00:27:53,680 --> 00:27:56,480
Why don't I have a visual on you?
Why can't I ever see you?

452
00:27:56,560 --> 00:27:59,240
Limited power, bad hair, take your pick.

453
00:27:59,320 --> 00:28:00,360
There's a door to your left, open it.

454
00:28:03,280 --> 00:28:05,200
Going to send you a map to that screen.

455
00:28:05,280 --> 00:28:07,640
I put your little friend somewhere safe,
I can get you to him.

456
00:28:07,960 --> 00:28:09,440
Rory? You found Rory?

457
00:28:09,520 --> 00:28:12,120
I call him Nina.
It's a personal thing. Hush, now.

458
00:28:17,520 --> 00:28:19,480
(WHISPERING) Who are you?

459
00:28:22,200 --> 00:28:23,600
Doctor...

460
00:28:28,440 --> 00:28:30,600
(FEMALE HUMMING)

461
00:28:31,760 --> 00:28:33,680
(MAN AND GIRL LAUGHING)

462
00:28:36,440 --> 00:28:37,880
(BABY CRYING)

463
00:28:39,800 --> 00:28:41,520
(HUMMING CONTINUES)

464
00:28:42,040 --> 00:28:43,360
(APPLAUSE)

465
00:28:52,520 --> 00:28:54,120
(HUMMING CONTINUES)

466
00:28:56,240 --> 00:28:58,600
How many Daleks
directly ahead of me right now?

467
00:29:00,800 --> 00:29:03,280
Ten, twenty? Hard to say.

468
00:29:03,800 --> 00:29:06,880
Some of them are catatonic
but they do have firepower.

469
00:29:06,960 --> 00:29:09,640
How do I get past them? Amy!

470
00:29:10,880 --> 00:29:13,800
Hmm, it's okay. Shh, it's okay.
It's just people in here.

471
00:29:13,880 --> 00:29:15,000
It's just people.

472
00:29:15,080 --> 00:29:17,880
Amy, it's the nanocloud.
It's altering your perception.

473
00:29:17,960 --> 00:29:20,840
Look again, look again.
Those aren't people.

474
00:29:22,840 --> 00:29:24,160
-(GASPS)
-Come here.

475
00:29:26,160 --> 00:29:29,000
Come on, Amy, take my hand. Run, run!

476
00:29:31,080 --> 00:29:32,720
No, they're coming down.

477
00:29:32,800 --> 00:29:35,320
Ah! Ah, yes, they are.

478
00:29:35,400 --> 00:29:36,840
(AMY SCREAMS)

479
00:29:37,480 --> 00:29:39,440
Intruder.

480
00:29:39,840 --> 00:29:41,800
-DOCTOR: Back.
-Intruder.

481
00:29:42,280 --> 00:29:45,400
(SLOWLY) Intruder.

482
00:29:47,360 --> 00:29:48,880
(POWERING DOWN)

483
00:30:01,320 --> 00:30:04,000
-It's damaged.
-Okay. But what do we do?

484
00:30:04,520 --> 00:30:07,280
Identify me, access your files.
Who am I?

485
00:30:08,040 --> 00:30:09,280
Come on!

486
00:30:09,760 --> 00:30:11,840
-Who's your daddy?
-You are

487
00:30:11,920 --> 00:30:13,520
the Predator.

488
00:30:13,600 --> 00:30:15,920
Access your standing orders
concerning the Predator.

489
00:30:16,000 --> 00:30:19,320
The Predator must be destroyed!

490
00:30:19,400 --> 00:30:21,520
And how are you going to do that?
Dalek without a gun?

491
00:30:21,600 --> 00:30:23,080
You're a tricycle with a roof.

492
00:30:23,400 --> 00:30:25,720
How are you going to destroy me?

493
00:30:26,640 --> 00:30:28,080
(ALARM BEEPING)

494
00:30:28,440 --> 00:30:31,520
Self-destruct initiated.

495
00:30:32,160 --> 00:30:33,760
AMY: What's it doing?

496
00:30:33,840 --> 00:30:36,120
It's going to blow itself up
and us with it.

497
00:30:36,200 --> 00:30:37,240
Only weapon it's got left.

498
00:30:37,320 --> 00:30:41,120
DALEK:
Self-destruct cannot be countermanded!

499
00:30:41,200 --> 00:30:43,800
DOCTOR:
I'm not looking for a countermand, dear.

500
00:30:43,880 --> 00:30:46,480
I'm looking for reverse.

501
00:30:46,560 --> 00:30:51,320
Forwards! Forwards! Forwards! Forwards/!

502
00:30:51,440 --> 00:30:53,360
-Forwards/!
-Intruder! Intruder!

503
00:30:57,200 --> 00:30:58,200
Whoa!

504
00:30:58,280 --> 00:30:59,320
(GASPS)

505
00:31:00,320 --> 00:31:04,320
Oswin, what was that? That was close.

506
00:31:11,920 --> 00:31:14,360
Oswin! What happened?

507
00:31:16,640 --> 00:31:18,360
Who killed all the Daleks?

508
00:31:26,800 --> 00:31:28,240
Who do you think?

509
00:31:34,200 --> 00:31:36,880
Will sleeping help her?
Will it slow down the process?

510
00:31:37,120 --> 00:31:38,240
You'd better hope so.

511
00:31:38,320 --> 00:31:40,840
Because pretty soon
she's going to try and kill you.

512
00:31:42,520 --> 00:31:44,480
-(AMY GROANS)
-DOCTOR: Amy.

513
00:31:44,640 --> 00:31:46,240
-Ow.
-DOCTOR: Amy.

514
00:31:46,560 --> 00:31:49,680
-You still with us?
-Amy, it's me.

515
00:31:51,960 --> 00:31:53,680
Do you remember me?

516
00:31:54,720 --> 00:31:56,320
-She remembers me.
-Same old Amy.

517
00:31:57,440 --> 00:32:00,320
Do you know
how you make someone into a Dalek?

518
00:32:00,400 --> 00:32:02,400
Subtract love, add anger.

519
00:32:04,080 --> 00:32:05,960
Doesn't she seem a bit too angry to you?

520
00:32:06,480 --> 00:32:09,080
Well, somebody's never been to Scotland.

521
00:32:09,280 --> 00:32:11,040
What about you though, Oswin?
How come you're okay?

522
00:32:11,120 --> 00:32:13,240
Why hasn't the nanocloud converted you?

523
00:32:13,320 --> 00:32:16,320
I mentioned the genius thing, yeah?
Shielded in here.

524
00:32:16,480 --> 00:32:20,520
Hmm. Clever of you. Now, this place.
The Daleks said it was fully automated.

525
00:32:21,120 --> 00:32:22,560
But look at it, it's a wreck.

526
00:32:22,880 --> 00:32:26,280
Well, I've had nearly a year
to mess with them. And...

527
00:32:27,080 --> 00:32:28,360
not a lot else to do.

528
00:32:28,440 --> 00:32:30,840
A junior entertainment manager
hiding out in a wrecked ship,

529
00:32:31,080 --> 00:32:34,640
hacking the security systems
of the most advanced warrior race

530
00:32:34,960 --> 00:32:36,840
the universe has ever seen.

531
00:32:36,920 --> 00:32:40,360
But you know what really
gets me about you, Oswin?

532
00:32:40,440 --> 00:32:41,960
The souffles.

533
00:32:42,040 --> 00:32:43,440
-The souffles?
-Where do you get milk

534
00:32:44,560 --> 00:32:45,600
for the souffles?

535
00:32:46,320 --> 00:32:47,920
Seriously, is no one else
wondering about that?

536
00:32:48,280 --> 00:32:50,680
No! Frankly, no. Twice.

537
00:32:50,880 --> 00:32:52,240
OSWIN: So, Doctor.

538
00:32:52,600 --> 00:32:54,720
I've been looking you up.
You're all over the database.

539
00:32:54,800 --> 00:32:56,480
Why do the Daleks call you the Predator?

540
00:32:56,600 --> 00:32:58,760
I'm not a predator.
I'm just a man with a plan.

541
00:32:59,000 --> 00:33:00,040
You've got a plan?

542
00:33:00,240 --> 00:33:01,360
We're all ears.

543
00:33:01,440 --> 00:33:03,800
There's a nose joke going
if someone wants to pick that one off.

544
00:33:03,880 --> 00:33:04,920
In no particular order,

545
00:33:05,000 --> 00:33:06,640
we need to neutralise
all the Daleks in this asylum,

546
00:33:06,720 --> 00:33:07,960
rescue Oswin from the wreckage,

547
00:33:08,040 --> 00:33:10,120
escape from this planet
and fix Amy and Rory's marriage.

548
00:33:11,800 --> 00:33:13,880
Okay, I'm counting three lost causes,
anyone else?

549
00:33:13,960 --> 00:33:15,880
DOCTOR:
Oswin, there's a Dalek ship in orbit.

550
00:33:15,960 --> 00:33:17,280
OSWIN: Yeah, got it on the sensors.

551
00:33:17,360 --> 00:33:18,600
The asylum has a force field.

552
00:33:18,680 --> 00:33:20,520
The Daleks upstairs
are waiting for me to turn it off.

553
00:33:20,600 --> 00:33:22,480
As soon as I do, they'll burn
this whole world and us with it.

554
00:33:22,640 --> 00:33:26,960
So, Oswin, my question is this,
how fast can you drop the force field?

555
00:33:29,120 --> 00:33:31,880
-What?
-Pretty fast.

556
00:33:32,640 --> 00:33:33,680
But why would I?

557
00:33:33,880 --> 00:33:35,720
Because this is a teleport,
am I right, Oswin?

558
00:33:35,960 --> 00:33:37,720
Yeah! Internal use only.

559
00:33:40,320 --> 00:33:44,160
I can boost the power, you know,
once the force field is down.

560
00:33:44,520 --> 00:33:47,320
And we can use this to beam us
right off this planet.

561
00:33:47,400 --> 00:33:48,920
But you said
when the force field is down,

562
00:33:49,000 --> 00:33:50,520
the Daleks will blow us up.

563
00:33:50,600 --> 00:33:51,640
We'll have to be quick, yes.

564
00:33:51,720 --> 00:33:53,440
Fine, we'll be quick,
but where do we beam to?

565
00:33:53,520 --> 00:33:54,560
The only place within range.

566
00:33:55,000 --> 00:33:56,120
The Dalek ship.

567
00:33:56,960 --> 00:33:58,960
Where they'd exterminate us on the spot.

568
00:33:59,040 --> 00:34:00,720
Oh, so this is the kind of escape plan

569
00:34:00,800 --> 00:34:02,520
where you survive
about four seconds longer?

570
00:34:02,600 --> 00:34:05,000
What's wrong with four seconds?
You can do loads in four seconds.

571
00:34:05,080 --> 00:34:07,200
Oswin, how fast can you drop
the force field?

572
00:34:07,800 --> 00:34:10,560
I can do it from here.
As soon as you come and get me.

573
00:34:12,840 --> 00:34:14,840
DOCTOR: No, just drop the force field
and come to us.

574
00:34:15,680 --> 00:34:17,480
There's enough power
in that teleport for one go.

575
00:34:17,560 --> 00:34:19,200
Why would you wait for me?

576
00:34:20,240 --> 00:34:21,360
Why wouldn't I?

577
00:34:22,040 --> 00:34:23,800
No idea, never met you.

578
00:34:23,880 --> 00:34:24,960
(TYPING)

579
00:34:25,040 --> 00:34:26,600
Sending you a map
So you can come get me.

580
00:34:27,920 --> 00:34:29,920
This place is crawling with Daleks.

581
00:34:30,040 --> 00:34:32,800
Yeah! Kind of why I'm anxious to leave.

582
00:34:33,200 --> 00:34:34,480
Come up and see me sometime.

583
00:34:36,960 --> 00:34:38,200
(BEEPING)

584
00:34:39,760 --> 00:34:40,800
So,

585
00:34:42,280 --> 00:34:43,440
are we going to go get her?

586
00:34:44,960 --> 00:34:47,400
I don't think that we have a choice.

587
00:34:50,520 --> 00:34:51,720
(SIGHS)

588
00:34:52,520 --> 00:34:54,120
DOCTOR: Okay, as soon as
the force field is down,

589
00:34:54,200 --> 00:34:55,560
the Daleks will attack.

590
00:34:55,640 --> 00:34:58,480
If it gets too explodey-wodey in here,
you go without me, okay?

591
00:34:58,560 --> 00:35:00,440
-And leave you to die?
-Oh, don't worry about me.

592
00:35:00,680 --> 00:35:02,880
You're the one beaming up to a
Dalek ship to get exterminated.

593
00:35:03,880 --> 00:35:06,480
Fair point. Love this plan.
What about Amy?

594
00:35:07,560 --> 00:35:10,200
Keep her remembering, keep her focused.

595
00:35:10,280 --> 00:35:11,440
That'll hold back the conversion.

596
00:35:11,520 --> 00:35:12,960
What do I do?

597
00:35:13,960 --> 00:35:15,400
You heard what she said.

598
00:35:15,480 --> 00:35:17,480
They're subtracting love.

599
00:35:17,880 --> 00:35:18,920
Don't let them.

600
00:35:23,320 --> 00:35:25,840
(DALEKS SHOUTING, MUFFLED)

601
00:35:26,200 --> 00:35:27,880
(POUNDING ON DOOR)

602
00:35:29,840 --> 00:35:33,200
DALEK: Prepare to be annihilated!

603
00:35:35,600 --> 00:35:36,840
(BANGING CONTINUES)

604
00:35:36,920 --> 00:35:39,880
DALEK: We are the Daleks!
We are the Daleks!

605
00:35:40,040 --> 00:35:41,960
We are the Daleks!

606
00:35:42,040 --> 00:35:43,440
(BEEPING)

607
00:35:48,000 --> 00:35:49,640
Okay, look at me.

608
00:35:51,760 --> 00:35:55,760
I'm going to be logical.
Cold and logical, okay?

609
00:35:55,840 --> 00:35:58,480
For both of our sakes, for both of us,

610
00:35:58,720 --> 00:36:00,720
I'm going to take this off my wrist
and put it on yours.

611
00:36:00,800 --> 00:36:03,040
Why? Then I'll just start
converting you. That's not better.

612
00:36:03,120 --> 00:36:05,680
Yeah, but it will buy us time
because it will take longer with me.

613
00:36:06,440 --> 00:36:07,480
Sorry, what?

614
00:36:07,560 --> 00:36:09,400
It subtracts love. That's what she said.

615
00:36:09,480 --> 00:36:11,560
What's that got to do with it?
What does that even mean?

616
00:36:11,640 --> 00:36:12,760
It's just arithmetic.

617
00:36:13,720 --> 00:36:16,160
It will take longer with me
because, well, we both know,

618
00:36:16,240 --> 00:36:18,400
we've both always known that...

619
00:36:21,400 --> 00:36:24,480
Amy, basic fact of our relationship is
that I love you more than you love me.

620
00:36:24,560 --> 00:36:27,920
Which today, is good news because
it might just save both of our lives.

621
00:36:29,880 --> 00:36:31,160
How can you say that?

622
00:36:31,680 --> 00:36:33,120
Two thousand years

623
00:36:33,200 --> 00:36:35,560
waiting for you outside a box,
saying it because it's true.

624
00:36:35,960 --> 00:36:37,680
And since you know it's true,
give me your arm.

625
00:36:37,760 --> 00:36:38,800
Amy!

626
00:36:40,960 --> 00:36:42,960
Don't you dare say that to me.
Don't you ever dare.

627
00:36:44,000 --> 00:36:46,000
-Amy, you kicked me out!
-You want kids.

628
00:36:46,160 --> 00:36:49,640
You have always wanted kids.
Ever since you were a kid.

629
00:36:52,040 --> 00:36:53,880
And I can't have them.

630
00:36:55,160 --> 00:36:58,320
-I know.
-Whatever they did to me at Demons Run,

631
00:36:59,240 --> 00:37:01,520
I can't ever give you children.

632
00:37:02,640 --> 00:37:04,480
I didn't kick you out,

633
00:37:05,960 --> 00:37:07,440
I gave you up.

634
00:37:10,160 --> 00:37:11,960
Amy, I don't...

635
00:37:12,040 --> 00:37:14,400
Don't you dare talk to me
about waiting outside a box

636
00:37:14,480 --> 00:37:19,680
because that is nothing, Rory, nothing
compared to giving you up.

637
00:37:20,920 --> 00:37:22,520
-Give me your arm. Let me put this on.
-Get off!

638
00:37:22,600 --> 00:37:24,080
-Just give me your arm!
-Don't touch me!

639
00:37:35,920 --> 00:37:37,600
It's the Doctor's.

640
00:37:38,720 --> 00:37:40,520
-When you were sleeping...
-A Time Lord.

641
00:37:41,360 --> 00:37:43,240
What's the betting
he doesn't even need it?

642
00:37:43,320 --> 00:37:45,640
Then why didn't he just tell us?

643
00:37:58,640 --> 00:37:59,800
Oswin,

644
00:38:00,840 --> 00:38:01,960
I think I'm close.

645
00:38:03,280 --> 00:38:04,320
You are!

646
00:38:05,760 --> 00:38:08,600
-Less than 20 feet away.
-(BEEPING)

647
00:38:10,400 --> 00:38:11,520
Which is the good news.

648
00:38:12,160 --> 00:38:13,280
Okay.

649
00:38:13,960 --> 00:38:15,480
And the bad,
which I suddenly feel is coming?

650
00:38:16,840 --> 00:38:18,920
You're about to pass
through Intensive Care.

651
00:38:35,640 --> 00:38:37,360
(SOFTLY) What's so special
about this lot, then?

652
00:38:37,440 --> 00:38:38,480
OSWIN: Don't know.

653
00:38:39,120 --> 00:38:40,840
Survivors of particular wars.

654
00:38:41,960 --> 00:38:46,240
Spiridon, Kembel, Aridius,
Vulcan, Exxilon.

655
00:38:47,120 --> 00:38:48,160
Ringing any bells?

656
00:38:49,040 --> 00:38:50,080
All of them.

657
00:38:50,240 --> 00:38:51,640
OSWIN: Yeah?

658
00:38:52,240 --> 00:38:53,600
How?

659
00:38:56,280 --> 00:38:58,880
These are the Daleks who survived me.

660
00:38:59,120 --> 00:39:00,560
DALEK: Doc...

661
00:39:01,840 --> 00:39:04,080
-...tor!
-Doc...

662
00:39:04,160 --> 00:39:06,440
-Doctor!
-...tor!

663
00:39:06,520 --> 00:39:09,680
ALL: Doctor!

664
00:39:09,760 --> 00:39:11,200
That's weird.

665
00:39:11,600 --> 00:39:13,680
Those ones don't usually
wake up for anything.

666
00:39:13,760 --> 00:39:16,480
Yeah, well, special visitor.

667
00:39:17,760 --> 00:39:18,880
Okay.

668
00:39:19,160 --> 00:39:20,280
Door,

669
00:39:20,680 --> 00:39:23,880
but it won't open.
They can't be far away now.

670
00:39:25,600 --> 00:39:26,840
Hang on, uh...

671
00:39:27,200 --> 00:39:29,600
Not quite sure but there's
a release code. Let me just...

672
00:39:29,960 --> 00:39:32,200
-Anything happening out there?
-No.

673
00:39:32,400 --> 00:39:34,040
Hang on, I'm trying to think.

674
00:39:43,120 --> 00:39:44,320
Doc...

675
00:39:46,200 --> 00:39:47,240
...tor!

676
00:39:50,000 --> 00:39:52,240
-Doctor!
-Doctor!

677
00:39:52,320 --> 00:39:54,000
-Doctor!
-Doctor!

678
00:39:54,080 --> 00:39:55,920
Oswin, get this door open.

679
00:39:56,520 --> 00:39:58,640
-Oswin, open this door!
-I can't!

680
00:39:58,920 --> 00:40:01,000
-Oswin!
-ALL: Doctor!

681
00:40:01,080 --> 00:40:03,080
DOCTOR: Please get this door open!

682
00:40:03,320 --> 00:40:05,720
DALEKS: Doctor!

683
00:40:05,800 --> 00:40:09,560
Oswin! Oswin, please get this door open!

684
00:40:10,080 --> 00:40:12,400
Help me! Help!

685
00:40:12,480 --> 00:40:14,200
(SILENCE)

686
00:40:14,600 --> 00:40:16,320
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

687
00:40:17,120 --> 00:40:19,080
OSWIN: Oh, that is cool.

688
00:40:19,400 --> 00:40:20,640
(OSWIN GIGGLING)

689
00:40:20,920 --> 00:40:22,680
Tell me I'm cool, chin boy.

690
00:40:24,320 --> 00:40:25,400
What did you do?

691
00:40:25,840 --> 00:40:27,280
Hang on.
I think I found the door thingy.

692
00:40:27,480 --> 00:40:29,240
No, tell me what you did.

693
00:40:29,320 --> 00:40:30,720
OSWIN: The Daleks,
they have a hive mind.

694
00:40:30,800 --> 00:40:32,680
Well they don't,
but they have a sort of telepathic web.

695
00:40:33,080 --> 00:40:34,120
The path web, yes.

696
00:40:34,320 --> 00:40:35,360
I hacked into it,

697
00:40:35,440 --> 00:40:37,560
did a master delete on all the
information connected with the Doctor.

698
00:40:38,720 --> 00:40:40,640
But you made them forget me.

699
00:40:40,720 --> 00:40:42,040
Good, huh?

700
00:40:42,360 --> 00:40:44,320
And here comes the door.

701
00:40:45,960 --> 00:40:48,080
I've tried hacking into the path web,
even I couldn't do it.

702
00:40:48,560 --> 00:40:50,320
Come and meet the girl who can.

703
00:40:53,600 --> 00:40:55,320
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

704
00:41:03,680 --> 00:41:04,800
Hey!

705
00:41:05,120 --> 00:41:06,520
You're right outside. Come on in.

706
00:41:06,840 --> 00:41:09,560
DOCTOR: Oswin, we have a problem.

707
00:41:11,280 --> 00:41:12,720
No, we don't.

708
00:41:13,280 --> 00:41:14,320
Don't even say that.

709
00:41:15,320 --> 00:41:16,360
I joined the Alaska to see the universe,

710
00:41:16,440 --> 00:41:18,360
ended up stuck in a shipwreck
first time out.

711
00:41:20,720 --> 00:41:23,520
Rescue me, chin boy,
and show me the stars.

712
00:41:23,640 --> 00:41:26,040
DOCTOR: Does it look real to you?

713
00:41:27,360 --> 00:41:29,720
-Does what look real?
-Where you are right now?

714
00:41:31,360 --> 00:41:32,440
Does it seem real?

715
00:41:32,760 --> 00:41:35,760
-It is real.
-It's a dream, Oswin.

716
00:41:37,560 --> 00:41:41,480
You dreamed it for yourself
because the truth was too terrible.

717
00:41:42,200 --> 00:41:43,360
Where am I?

718
00:41:51,560 --> 00:41:53,920
Where am I?

719
00:41:54,600 --> 00:41:57,200
Where am I?

720
00:41:57,360 --> 00:41:59,880
Because you are a Dalek.

721
00:42:01,480 --> 00:42:03,040
I am not a...

722
00:42:03,200 --> 00:42:06,080
...Dalek. I am not a Dalek/

723
00:42:06,280 --> 00:42:07,520
I'm human.

724
00:42:08,120 --> 00:42:10,080
You were human when you crashed here.

725
00:42:10,160 --> 00:42:13,880
It was you who climbed out of the pod.

726
00:42:14,160 --> 00:42:15,960
That was your ladder.

727
00:42:21,920 --> 00:42:23,240
Where am I? Where am I?

728
00:42:24,640 --> 00:42:25,680
Where am I?

729
00:42:27,160 --> 00:42:29,120
I'm human.

730
00:42:29,400 --> 00:42:30,800
Not any more.

731
00:42:31,840 --> 00:42:33,640
Because you're right.

732
00:42:34,240 --> 00:42:35,840
You're a genius.

733
00:42:36,720 --> 00:42:38,960
And the Daleks need genius.

734
00:42:40,600 --> 00:42:43,000
They didn't just make you a puppet.

735
00:42:45,360 --> 00:42:47,040
They did a full conversion.

736
00:42:49,360 --> 00:42:51,840
Where am I? Where am I?

737
00:42:52,320 --> 00:42:53,520
Where am I?

738
00:42:54,280 --> 00:42:56,000
Oswin, I am so sorry.

739
00:42:58,440 --> 00:42:59,800
But you are a Dalek.

740
00:43:00,200 --> 00:43:01,800
The milk Oswin.

741
00:43:02,040 --> 00:43:06,640
The milk and the eggs for the souffles.
Where? Where did it all come from?

742
00:43:07,160 --> 00:43:08,880
Eggs. I'm human.

743
00:43:09,560 --> 00:43:12,240
I am not a Dalek.
I am human. I am not Dalek.

744
00:43:12,400 --> 00:43:13,440
I am human!

745
00:43:15,040 --> 00:43:16,480
IIEggs.-- Fr

746
00:43:17,560 --> 00:43:19,080
It wasn't real.

747
00:43:20,320 --> 00:43:21,600
It was never real.

748
00:43:23,640 --> 00:43:25,560
I am a Dalek. I am a Dalek.

749
00:43:26,800 --> 00:43:28,320
IIEggs.-- Fr

750
00:43:29,080 --> 00:43:30,400
...term...

751
00:43:31,480 --> 00:43:34,120
ed.. 1707,

752
00:43:34,520 --> 00:43:36,040
-Oswin?
-Ex...

753
00:43:36,320 --> 00:43:39,160
...ter...minate.

754
00:43:39,720 --> 00:43:41,560
-Exterminate!
-Oswin.

755
00:43:41,640 --> 00:43:43,800
-No, no, no, Oswin? Oswin.
-Exterminate! Exterminate!

756
00:43:43,880 --> 00:43:47,160
Listen, Oswin.
You don't have to do this. Oswin?

757
00:43:47,240 --> 00:43:48,400
Oswin!

758
00:43:48,520 --> 00:43:50,360
(SPEECH GARBLED)

759
00:43:53,200 --> 00:43:54,480
(SOBBING)

760
00:44:05,800 --> 00:44:07,000
Why do they hate you...

761
00:44:07,720 --> 00:44:09,120
...so much?

762
00:44:09,200 --> 00:44:12,880
They hate you so much.

763
00:44:13,040 --> 00:44:14,080
Why?

764
00:44:16,240 --> 00:44:17,680
I have fought them

765
00:44:18,400 --> 00:44:20,560
many, many times.

766
00:44:21,000 --> 00:44:24,600
We have grown stronger

767
00:44:24,960 --> 00:44:27,720
in fear of you.

768
00:44:29,440 --> 00:44:30,640
I know.

769
00:44:32,600 --> 00:44:34,000
I tried to stop.

770
00:44:38,040 --> 00:44:39,080
Then run.

771
00:44:41,080 --> 00:44:42,200
What did you say?

772
00:44:43,920 --> 00:44:45,320
I've taken down the force field.

773
00:44:45,520 --> 00:44:49,400
The Daleks above
have begun their attack. Run!

774
00:44:49,640 --> 00:44:52,960
-Oswin, are you...
-I am Oswin Oswald.

775
00:44:53,040 --> 00:44:55,200
I fought the Daleks and I am...

776
00:44:55,280 --> 00:44:56,760
...human.

777
00:44:57,160 --> 00:44:59,800
Remember me.

778
00:45:01,200 --> 00:45:03,040
-Thank you.
-Run!

779
00:45:03,560 --> 00:45:04,920
(EXPLOSION)

780
00:45:08,640 --> 00:45:10,840
(SOFTLY) Run, you clever boy.

781
00:45:13,000 --> 00:45:14,440
And remember.

782
00:45:23,840 --> 00:45:25,320
(BOTH GASPING)

783
00:45:28,480 --> 00:45:29,640
How long can we wait?

784
00:45:33,120 --> 00:45:34,800
The rest of our lives.

785
00:45:37,960 --> 00:45:39,000
Agreed.

786
00:45:51,280 --> 00:45:52,840
Right! Let's go!

787
00:45:53,160 --> 00:45:54,400
Let's go.

788
00:45:55,240 --> 00:45:56,680
We're good. Let's go.

789
00:45:58,800 --> 00:46:00,960
-For God's sake.
-(BEEPS)

790
00:46:10,040 --> 00:46:12,920
DALEX: The asylum is destroyed.

791
00:46:13,200 --> 00:46:17,840
Incoming teleport from asylum planet.
We are under attack.

792
00:46:18,600 --> 00:46:22,880
DALEK SUPREME: Prepare to defend.
Defend! Defend!

793
00:46:23,280 --> 00:46:26,120
Explain, Dalek Supreme.

794
00:46:26,200 --> 00:46:28,160
DOCTOR: You know, you guys
should really have seen this coming.

795
00:46:28,840 --> 00:46:32,080
The thing about me and teleport,
I've got a really good aim.

796
00:46:32,160 --> 00:46:34,120
Pinpoint accurate, in fact.

797
00:46:34,280 --> 00:46:36,560
Or, to put it another way...

798
00:46:38,280 --> 00:46:39,360
Suckers!

799
00:46:39,440 --> 00:46:41,200
DALEK: Identify yourself.

800
00:46:41,440 --> 00:46:44,440
-Identify!
-Identify!

801
00:46:44,520 --> 00:46:49,160
It's me. You know me, the Doctor.
The oncoming storm. The Predator.

802
00:46:49,640 --> 00:46:51,640
DARLA: Titles are not meaningful
in this context.

803
00:46:52,800 --> 00:46:53,840
Doctor who?

804
00:46:54,280 --> 00:46:55,760
Doctor who?

805
00:46:56,040 --> 00:46:57,520
DALEK: Doctor who?

806
00:46:57,600 --> 00:46:59,840
-Oh, Oswin.
-Doctor who?

807
00:46:59,920 --> 00:47:02,000
Oh, you did it to them all.

808
00:47:03,080 --> 00:47:05,400
You beauty.

809
00:47:05,760 --> 00:47:09,880
DALEKS: Doctor who? Doctor who?

810
00:47:09,960 --> 00:47:12,720
Fellas, you're never going to
stop asking.

811
00:47:13,000 --> 00:47:15,280
(CHANTING CONTINUES)

812
00:47:28,400 --> 00:47:29,480
Yes!

813
00:47:30,000 --> 00:47:31,520
-I can see you.
-Okay.

814
00:47:36,440 --> 00:47:37,800
Doctor Who!

815
00:47:41,920 --> 00:47:43,520
Doctor Who!

816
00:47:45,600 --> 00:47:49,000
Doctor... Who!

817
00:47:52,480 --> 00:47:54,720
MAN: This ship contains
the most precious cargo.

818
00:47:54,800 --> 00:47:56,240
WOMAN: The ship's coming
through the atmosphere.

819
00:47:56,640 --> 00:47:59,960
The creatures on board this ship
are not objects to be sold or traded.

820
00:48:00,040 --> 00:48:01,400
-Who sent you?
-That's my dad.

821
00:48:01,480 --> 00:48:02,520
What's going on?

822
00:48:02,600 --> 00:48:03,640
(CREATURE SCREECHING)

823
00:48:03,720 --> 00:48:05,040
This ship's been boarded before.

824
00:48:05,120 --> 00:48:08,000
You think I won't punish those
who get in my way?

825
00:48:08,080 --> 00:48:09,280
WOMAN: I'm launching the missiles.

826
00:48:10,600 --> 00:48:11,720
What was your name again?

827
00:48:12,040 --> 00:48:13,800
Whatever's down there
is coming this way.

828
00:48:13,880 --> 00:48:15,720
Queen Nefertiti of Egypt.

829
00:48:16,800 --> 00:48:20,440
-What is it?
-Dinosaurs, on a spaceship!

830
00:48:20,520 --> 00:48:21,560
(GROWLING)

